        <h3 id="DDos">Distributed denial of service (DDOs) attack</h3>

        <strong>What is a DDoS attack?</strong>
        <p>
            The botnet will direct large volumes of traffic at a web server in the attempt to overwhelm so that it
            cannot respoind to legitimate requests.
        </p>

        <strong>How does a DDos attack generate revenue?</strong>
        <p>
            A commonly used technique is where the botmaster initiated an attack on a website, proving they have the
            capability to overwhelm their servers.
            The botmaster will then extort 'protection' in exchange for not launching another larger or more widespread
            attack on their site.
            The websites most commonly targeted using this technique will be websites reliant on large events such as
            the World Cup or the Olympics to generate revenue.
        </p>
        <!--DDOS END-->

