        <!--PPC START -->
        <h3 id="ppcFraud">PPC fraud</h3>

        <strong>What is Pay Per Click (PPC)?</strong>
        <p>
            PPC is an internet advertising model in which the publisher or host of the website will show an advert on
            their site in exchange for a payment respective to the number of users directed to the advertised site from
            the advert.

        </p>

        <strong>How does a Botnet exploit PPC?</strong>
        <ul>
            <li>The botmaster will set up a website that appears to be legitimate in order to recruit a legitimate
                advertiser.
            </li>
            <li>The botmaster can then utilise their many computers in their botnet to visit the fake website and click
                on the advert.
            </li>
            <li>The clicks will appear as genuine customer traffic due to the thousands of computers in the botnet in
                geographically different locations, which the advertiser will then pay for.
            </li>

        </ul>
        <!--PPC END-->

